    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.7.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n`cat sample.lua`\r\n```lua\r\n-- smart dd\r\nfunction smart_dd()\r\n    return ''\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'dd', smart_dd, {noremap = true, expr = true})\r\n```\r\n\r\n`cat script.lua`\r\n```lua\r\nlocal bufnr = 1\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_call(bufnr, function()\r\n    vim.cmd('2,4fold')\r\n    vim.cmd('5delete')\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_text(0, 0, 0, 4, 66, {\r\n        '-- smart dd',\r\n        'function smart_dd()',\r\n        '    return \"\"',\r\n        'end',\r\n        '',\r\n        'vim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"dd\", smart_dd, { noremap = true, expr = true })',\r\n        ''\r\n    })\r\nend)\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. `nvim --clean sample.lua +'so script.lua'`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nlines `2-4` are folded.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nlines `4-6` are folded.",
